# PPRC

pprc is peer-to-peer relay chat programme,
written in ANSI C, based on UDP.

## Syntax

```
pprc c [id] [server]
```

Establish connection to peer via hole-punching.
Each peer must share session id.
UNIX user name will be used to identify you with your ip.

```
pprc d [dest-ip] [dest-port] [port]
```

Establish connection directly to peer.
UNIX user name will be used to identify you with your ip.

```
pprc s
```

Open hole-punching server.

## Requisites

- OpenSSL

## Compiling

```
make -j `nproc`
```

...and, use pprc in your source directory!
